[normal] [bold]DFID [bold]activities [bold]in Afghanistan[bold]:[bold]As far as I know DFID
[normal] in Afghanistan,
[normal] they are spending
[normal] for supporting the government,
[normal] and
[normal] also providing
[normal] 
[normal]huge support
[normal] to 
[normal]International Organization as implementing partners for developmental and humanitarian’s
[normal] affair
[normal]. For Afghan disabled people NGOs,
[normal] 
[normal]they have very limited support to persons with disability in Afghanistan.
[normal] I several time knocked the door of DFID in Afghanistan
[normal],
[normal] they
[normal] only
[normal] said that we are supporting the International Organizations not have so far plan to support local NGOs. 
[normal]There are very limited NGOs running by persons with disability 
[normal]working 
[normal]for 
[normal]the 
[normal]mission and vision to support persons with disability
[normal] in Afghanistan
[normal]. I
[normal]n the present context
[normal], many of the Afghan disabled people organization are collapsed
[normal] due to the 2014
[normal] alarm of the media. 
[normal] 
[normal]The Afghan government has no systems to support the 
[normal]Afghan 
[normal]CSOs, DPOs and NGOs
[normal]. Several Afghan NGOs working for persons with disability has 
[normal]shortage of
[normal] funding for 
[normal]their 
[normal]activities and administrative support 
[normal]because;
[normal] the 
[normal]donor’s
[normal] agencies are not interesting to support disability development activities
[normal] in Afghanistan because, it is not related to politics
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
